## Proposed refactor for `src/Card.tsx`

```tsx
import styles from "./Card.module.css";

type CardProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  onActivate: () => void;
};

export function Card({ children, onActivate }: CardProps) {
  return (
    <button type="button" className={styles.card} onClick={onActivate}>
      <div className={styles.body}>{children}</div>
      <aside className={styles.sidebar}>sidebar</aside>
    </button>
  );
}
```

```css
/* Card.module.css */
.card {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--size-card-max, 64rem);   /* was 800px hard cap */
  padding: var(--space-6);
  background: var(--color-surface-accent);  /* was #ff00aa */
  color: var(--color-fg-default);           /* was #0a0a0a */
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);    /* was #cccccc */
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);             /* was 0 2px 4px rgb(0,0,0) */
  outline-color: var(--color-focus-ring);   /* was #1a73e8 */
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 15rem;
  gap: var(--space-4);
}

.body {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 1vw + 0.875rem, 1.125rem); /* was 18px fixed */
  color: var(--color-fg-muted);
}

.sidebar { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); color: var(--color-fg-subtle); }

@media (max-width: 40rem) {
  .card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }     /* collapse on mobile */
}
```

### How each change maps to a finding

| Finding | Change |
|---|---|
| **`accessible_interaction_risk`** (crime_00001) — `<div onClick>` is unreachable by keyboard/screen reader | Promoted the outer element to `<button type="button">` with a named `onActivate` prop. Keyboard focus, Enter/Space activation, and accessible role come for free — no `role`/`tabIndex`/key-handler band-aid needed. |
| **`design_token_escape`** (crime_00002) — 9 raw literals across color/px/rgb/shadow | Every literal replaced with a CSS custom property (`--color-*`, `--space-*`, `--shadow-*`). Future agents extending the component now have to *name* what they want, which makes drift visible in review. |
| **`responsive_fragility`** (crime_00003) — `width: 800px`, `width: 720px`, `fontSize: 18px`, no `@media` | Outer `width: 800` → `width: 100%` + `max-width` in `rem`. Inner `width: 720` → `minmax(0, 1fr)` grid column. `fontSize: 18` → `clamp()` so it scales with viewport. Added an `@media (max-width: 40rem)` rule that collapses the sidebar so the layout works on phones. |

### Notes on agent-risk impact

- Replacing the `<div onClick>` with a `<button>` also removes a *silent* a11y trap an LLM is likely to copy-forward when adding a second clickable region — the new shape forces correct semantics by construction.
- Moving styles out of inline `style={{}}` into a CSS module means scoring will no longer keep tripping on this file every time someone tweaks a color; the detector's evidence surface drops to zero.
- The new `onActivate` prop name is deliberately behavior-named rather than `onClick`, so the call site reads as an intent rather than a DOM event — easier for agents to wire to keyboard shortcuts later.
